The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Thursday, April 22, 2004  Good Morning Hello It's Thursday, April 22, 2004				 																Road to avoid 				 																																	Prince Anwar Shah Road. One flank on the western end dug up to lay waterlines.				 																Discussion				 																																	A public panel discussion on Fly Over Calcutta: Visions for the Megapolis, hosted by Max Mueller Bhavan, in association with The Telegraph, at GD Birla Sabhagar, at 6.30 pm. Speakers include Mrinal Sen, Barun De, Bonani Kakkar and Mansoor Nazeer. Sunanda K. Datta-Ray will moderate.				 																																	An international conference on Does culture make a difference?, organised by Max Mueller Bhavan and The German Agency for Technical Cooperation, supported by the United Nations and in association with The Telegraph, at Taj Bengal, 9.30 am.				 																																	An interactive session for teachers, students and guardians on India is shining  is it because of our education system, or in spite of it?, organised by Ladies Study Group, at Vidya Mandir, at 3.30 pm.				 																Screening				 																																	Matir Moina, directed by Tareque Masud, will be screened as part of Cinema in celebration of life at Gorky Sadan, at 6 pm.				 																Soiree				 																																	Bangladeshi singer Iffat Ara Dewan will perform at MusicWorld on Park Street, at 5 pm. 				 																Art beat				 																																	An exhibition of paintings by Rabindramohon Nayak on display at Bharatiyam, 4 pm to 8 pm.				 																																	An exhibition of terracotta sculptures by Shyamal Roy and Thakurnanda Pal on view at Gallery Kanishkas, from 11 am to 8 pm.
